content:
Migrate to a Multiple-Configuration SAML Framework (Release Update)

This release update removes support for the single-configuration SAML framework and supports only the multiple-configuration SAML framework. To preserve your existing configuration, follow the steps to apply this update.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

When: This update is enforced for production instances in Spring ’25 and is enforced for sandboxes in Summer ’24.

Why: We’re no longer supporting the single-configuration SAML SSO framework that you’re currently using. When this update is enforced, you’re required to use a multiple-configuration SAML framework.

How: 

* SAML responses from your identity provider must include the audience attribute.
* Your Salesforce Login URL changes.
* If Salesforce can’t parse a SAML response, it isn’t recorded in the login history.

Make sure you understand these changes, update your configuration accordingly, and test all changes in a sandbox before enabling this update.
title: Migrating from Single-Configuration SAML to Multiple-Configuration
